item.title: R to @0xB100B01D: I've seen them in Issaquah and once in Crossroads. For a while there was a breeding pair on Mercer Island, but on the whole they are scant. You will 100% see them if you travel East or if you increase in elevation (i.e. take a trip to Rainier, North Cascades, etc.)

item.title: Ready for the #CrowOrNoReveal? Today's bird is a big ol' No Crow. It's a common raven. Key features are the big bill & hackles. While the texture of the hackle feather themselves aren't so obvious that bump is. Crows really have to be doing work to get a silhouette like that.
